Pupils at the Mugoidwa Secondary School are now in classes, but some are forced to share their chairs and tables. VUWANI Matric pupils in Vuwani say they are determined to perform well in this year s exams despite returning to vandalised buildings. Some schools were burnt down during protests over demarcation issues last year.While the Basic Education Department provided over 70 mobile classrooms to affected schools, some pupils are now in classes without chairs and tables.Pupils at the Mugoidwa Secondary School are now in classes, but some are forced to share their chairs and tables.Some of the school s furniture was reduced to ashes during violent protests in the area last year.But pupils say this will not stop them from obtaining good results.The school principal says he s discussed the shortage of furniture with the Basic Education Department. (Edited by Leeto M Khoza)